<HEADLINE> Two U.S. High School Football Players Die </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 13 (Xinhua)-- Two U.S. high school
football players died from injuries suffered earlier this month,
according to press report reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
Chandler Craig and Russell Larabell, died Sunday night when
they were removed from life-support systems. Both were 16 years
old.
</P>
<P>
Craig, a middle linebacker for Hamilton High School, was
injured making a tackle in a 19-12 homecoming victory on October
2.
</P>
<P>
Larabell had been in a coma since he collapsed on October 1
after a Naples High junior varsity game against Barron Collier
High. He played last season as a freshman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
