<HEADLINE> Ackerman Named Female Sports Executive of the Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 13 (Xinhua)-- Val Ackerman, president of
the WNBA, was named Female Sports Executive of the Year by Sports
Business Journal Magazine.
</P>
<P>
She has headed the summertime women's professional basketball
league since its inception two years ago.
</P>
<P>
Teams are averaging more than 10,000 fans a game. Ackerman
received 25.7% of the vote in the poll conducted for the magazine
by a intersearch organization.
</P>
<P>
Susan O'Malley, president of Washington Sports and
Entertainment, was second, followed by Donna Lopiano, director of
the Women's Sports Foundation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
