<HEADLINE> Beijing International Music Festival Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 13 (Xinhua) -- The '98 Beijing International
Music Festival was held tonight in Beijing's Great Hall of the
People.
</P>
<P>
The conductor of the Berlin Radio Orchestra thrilled the local
audience with Beethoven's Symphony No.3 in a flat major op.55
"Eroica" and the No.5 piano concerto.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Li Lanqing, also a member of the Standing
Committee of the Political Bureau of the Communist Party of China
(CPC) Central Committee, joined over 6,000 music afficionados at
tonights performance.
</P>
<P>
Chinese musicians and musicians from Germany, Australia,
England, France, Russia, the United States, Poland and Japan will
stage 21 concerts over the next two weeks.  
</P>
</TEXT>
