<HEADLINE> Vietnamese Communist Party Holds Sixth Plenum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, October 13 (Xinhua) -- The sixth plenum of the eighth
Central Committee of the Communist Party of Vietnam opened here
Tuesday morning.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnam News Agency (VNA) said the plenum is to review the
implementation of the country's socio-economic targets for this
year, and devise orientation and tasks for development for the
next year.
</P>
<P>
The plenum is also to discuss how to push forward agriculture
and rural development.
</P>
<P>
Party General Secretary Le Kha Phieu delivered a key note
speech at the opening session, presenting the Political Bureau's
opinions, and bringing issues for discussion during the session.
</P>
<P>
Permanent politburo member and Prime Minister Phan Van Khai
presented a report on issues related to national socio-economic
development.
</P>
<P>
Participants at the plenum were briefed on the socio-economic
development, budget balance, agriculture and rural development of
the country.
</P>
<P>
However, the official news agency gave no details of Phieu's
speech and Khai's report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
