<HEADLINE> Cyprus, Slovakia Sign Air Cooperation Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus and Slovakia signed an
air cooperation agreement here Tuesday as part of efforts to
strengthen bilateral economic ties.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the airlines of the two countries were
allowed to fly regular flights between Cyprus and Slovakia with
full commercial rights to transport passengers, cargo and post.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed by Cyprus Communications and Works
Minister Leontios Ierodiaconou and visiting Slovak Minister of
Transport, Posts and Telecommunications Jan Jasovsky.
</P>
<P>
Ierodiakonou said the agreement will contribute to the
development in the air transport and boost tourism and trade
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Jasovsky also said the agreement will strengthen cooperation
between the two countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
