<HEADLINE> Share Prices Unchanged on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Share prices almost remained
unchanged on Singapore Stock Market Tuesday as the benchmark
Straits Times Index (STI) inched down 0.96 points to end at
1015.64 points in active trading.
</P>
<P>
The total turnover was 231.80 million units valued at 363.82
million Singapore dollars (about 223.20 million U.S. dollars).
There were 183 losers against 55 gainers with 182 counters
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
DBS Land was the most actively traded stock of the day as it
had a volume of 14.50 million units traded. Wing T was the second
most active stock with a volume of 10.91 million units. Ho Pro was
next with 10.18 million counters changing hands
</P>
<P>
ClipSal led the ascent of the day with a rise of 21 cents to
1.00 U.S. dollars at close. Jurship moved up 20 cents to end at
6.80 Singapore dollars. SPH was also up 20 cents and ended at
14.90 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, CityDev was the biggest loser of the day as it
lost 32 cents to close at 4.44 Singapore dollars. Venture w99 was
slid 30 cents to 3.50 Singapore dollars. Cerebos shed off 10 cents
to end 2.26 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said investors locked in their profits after several
days of gains.
</P>
<P>
They said hopes for further interest rate cuts, expectations
that some companies will implement share buyback schemes and Wall
Street's overnight strength cushioned the index decline.
</P>
<P>
The STI rebounded from an intra-day low of 1004.97 points and
the Index is fairly resilient, said an institutional trader.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
