<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, October 13 (Xinhua) -- South Africa Tuesday
launched an 85-million Rand (about 12 million U.S. Dollars) rural
anti-poverty project, expecting to create more than 14,000 jobs,
South African Public Works Minister Jeff Radebe said.
</P>
<P>
Radebe was speaking at the launch of the project by President
Nelson Mandela at Ezingolweni on the KwaZulu Natal Province.
</P>
