<HEADLINE> Greek Equities Rebound Strongly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Greek equities Tuesday rebounded
strongly on the Athens Stock Exchange with the general index
ending 2.46 percent higher to 1,782.49 points.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE/ASE 20 index also ended 2.46 percent higher to
1,055.49 points.
</P>
<P>
Trading remained thin with turnover at 29.3 billion drachmas
(about 103 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Advancers led decliners by 174 to 49 with another 19 issues
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Banks and industrials rose 2.60 percent and 2.53 percent
respectively, with construction increasing 1.45 percent.
</P>
<P>
Last week, Greek equities came under pressure on the Athens
Stock Exchange with the general index falling below the 1,800
level for the first time in seven months this year.
</P>
<P>
Financial analysts attributed the decline to continued
uncertainty of international financial markets and the sudden
increase in Greece's inflation, which currently stands at 5.2
percent. 
