<HEADLINE> Natural Fires Hit Many Areas in Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Many mountainous and coastal
areas through Lebanon were hit by raging natural fires on Tuesday,
the official National News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
It said that Lebanon's northern, central and southern
mountainous and southern coastal areas were affected by the fires
and more than 1 million square meters of forests have been
destroyed.
</P>
<P>
The worst thing is that the fires have threatened the
country's symbolic cedar trees of the national reserve in the
central Chouf Mountain.
</P>
<P>
Firefighters, civil defense units and government army have
been sent to the affected areas to join efforts with local
residents to fight the fires, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
Lebanon's Environment Ministry officials attributed the quickly
spreading fires to the sustained heat wave and severe shortage of
adequate fire fighting equipment. 
