<HEADLINE> Azeri President: Elections Democratic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Azeri President Geidar Aliyev
said Tuesday that the Sunday presidential elections were
democratic despite minor offenses, the Interfax news agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
Aliyev, who was reelected president, refuted the view of the
Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe and the
Council of Europe Parliamentary Assembly observers that the
elections had not met international standards.
</P>
<P>
