called on opposition leaders to work for national unity but said
that none of his rivals in the presidential elections would become
a government minister.
</P>
<P>
Aliyev, 75, pocketed 77 percent of the ballots cast at the
presidential elections, well over the two-thirds needed for a win.
</P>
<P>
Aliyev was elected president of this Caspian oil-rich country
for the first time in 1993. 
