<HEADLINE> Kenyan Currency Edges Up on Export Earnings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, October 13 (Xinhua) -- The Kenyan Shilling edged up
against the U.S. Dollar in thin trade Tuesday as Dollar inflows
dealers.
</P>
<P>
The Shilling was quoted between 59.85 and 59.95 at 0930 GMT
Tuesday, from around 59.90/60.00 at the open.
</P>
<P>
"Even a small amount (of Dollar inflow) is enough to move the
Shilling," said one dealer.
</P>
<P>
The traders said that the low trading volume could be partly
explained by this week's planned motion of no confidence in the
government.
</P>
<P>
The bill, proposed by opposition member of parliament James
Orengo, is expected to be mentioned Wednesday and debated
Thursday, according to local media.
</P>
<P>
Analysts here say that it has little or no chance of success.
</P>
<P>
"Activity is subdued," said one trader. "People are watching
to see what happens tomorrow (Wednesday)."
</P>
<P>
The Central Bank of Kenya posted the Shilling at an opening
indicative mean of 59.9483 against the U.S. Dollar Tuesday from
59.9222 at Monday's open. 
</P>
