<HEADLINE> Accord Is Lasting Basis for Solution, Milosevic Says </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslav President Slobodan
Milosevic said on Tuesday an agreement was a "lasting basis for a
solution" to the crisis of Serbia's southern province of Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued from Milosevic's office said a constructive
approach "has been shown that can indubitably represent the
lasting basis for a political solution of autonomy for Kosovo
within Serbia."
</P>
<P>
"The steps which our country is taking to peacefully solve the
problem in Kosovo show our country's firm commitment to overcoming
this problem by political means, as well as its determination to
defend its territorial integrity and sovereignty," said the
statement which was reported by Yugoslav news agency Tanjug.
</P>
<P>
After nine-day tough talks, Milosevic and U.S. special envoy
reached an agreement which allows the presence of international
observers in Kosovo and the return of ethnic Albanian refugees
back home.
</P>
<P>
Milosevic's statement said the talks "focused on the
international community's insistence that specific steps be taken
to ensure the permanent observation and verification of the
development of the situation in Kosovo."
</P>
<P>
It added that the task of verification should be carried out by
a mission from the Organization of Security and Cooperation for
Europe (OSCE). A 2000-strong OSCE force is expected to be deployed
in Kosovo to ensure the compliance of U.N. resolution.
</P>
<P>
"Yugoslavia expects that this would eliminate erroneous,
incorrect and ill-intentioned reports of events in Kosovo," it
added.
</P>
<P>
It also said the agreement to allow OSCE mission "will
undoubtedly form the basis of a lasting political solution for
Kosovo's autonomy within Serbia." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
