<HEADLINE> Hungary Welcomes Political Solution to Kosovo Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Hungary welcomes the U.S.-
Yugoslav agreement which put on hold a possible NATO air strike
against Yugoslavia over the Kosovo crisis, a senior Hungarian
government official said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued at the official Hungarian Journal,
Hungarian Foreign Minister Martonyi Janos said his government
believed more than ever that the Kosovo crisis could be finalized
through a political solution.
</P>
<P>
He said that Hungary also welcomed a delayed deadline for the
implementation of U.N. resolution, which, he said, would help
prompt new possibilities for a peaceful end in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
NATO on Tuesday night authorized air strikes on Yugoslavia at
any time but gave Yugoslav government four days' grace to comply
with all U.N. demands which also include the free access of
international aid agencies in Kosovo and allow thousands of
refugees to go back home.
</P>
<P>
Following the NATO decision, Yugoslav President Slobodan
Milosevic reached an agreement with U.S. special envoy Richard
Holbrooke, which guarantees the withdrawal of Serbian security
forces from Kosovo.  
