<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Exchange Students in Canada Suffers Extensive Abuse </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Two British police officers have
uncovered more than 500 cases of sexual and physical abuse which
happened to international exchange students in Canada, the Globe
and Mail newspaper reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Detective Chief Inspector Chris Gould and Detective Constable
Kaye Jones have traveled the world for the past four months as
part of their ongoing investigation into the abuse of children on
foreign exchange trips.
</P>
<P>
"This is happening to children around the world, including
Canada," said Gould.
</P>
<P>
Gould and Jones have seen everything from a host family feeding
their exchange students nothing but bread and jam to cases where
convicted children-abusers host exchange students so they can have
free and easy access to children.
</P>
<P>
The study was presented at an Interpol conference on child
abuse in Ottawa last week.
</P>
<P>
The two British officers said among the 500 cases uncovered so
far, only three had ever been reported to police.
</P>
<P>
"Because of the distance from home, the strange environment and
the difficulty for the exchange students, these abuses can be
going on without anyone knowing," said Gould.
</P>
<P>
Among the cases, there was a 17-year-old girl from Australia
who arrived at a small community outside Toronto in 1995. She was
raped by the son of her host family.
</P>
<P>
When the girl reported the rape to the Toronto-based program's
coordinator, she was transferred to another host family and told
not to mention the incident again.
</P>
<P>
The crime was never reported to police and the boy's parents
were never told. And the family can continue to host foreign
exchange students.
</P>
<P>
Gould and Jones are pushing for some sort of government body to
oversee the agencies which operate student exchange programs. They
also recommend parents do their research before allowing their
children to take a company or school trip overseas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981014.0044 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-14 </DATE_TIME>
