<HEADLINE> China Exports Digital Switching Systems to Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, October 14 (Xinhua) -- China National Constructional and
Agricultural Machinery Import and Export Corporation (CAMC) signed
a contract here Wednesday with Bangladesh Telegraph and Telephone
Board (BTTB) on providing digital switching systems to Bangladesh.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement signed between Zhao Jinying, chief
representative of CAMC in Bangladesh, and BTTB Chairman M.A.
Mannan Chowdhury, CAMC will provide and install digital switching
systems of 16,050 lines for BTTB.
</P>
<P>
The switching systems will be installed in Prime Minister
Sheikh Hasina's home district of Gopalganj in southwestern
Bangladesh, and in nine other districts across the country.
</P>
<P>
The project will be completed within one year.
</P>
<P>
This is the second time for China-made digital switching
systems to be exported to Bangladesh. 
</P>
