<HEADLINE> Beijing Enterprises Holdings Unveils Bold High-tech </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Beijing Enterprises Holdings,
the listing arm of the Beijing municipal government, unveiled
here Wednesday a series of strategic initiatives in high
technology with a capital commitment of about 200 million HK
dollars (25.6 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
High technology has been one of the company's four core
businesses since its listing in Hong Kong last year, Chairman of
the company Hu Zhaoguang noted, expecting the new investments to
generate growth opportunities for his company,
</P>
<P>
Among the initiatives was the establishment of a venture
capital fund, with an initial target of 50 million U.S. dollars,
to explore high technology opportunities. A memorandum of
understanding with WI Harper, a U.S. venture capital firm, was
signed in this regard, Hu told a press conference Wednesday
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Enterprises Holdings also entered into a joint venture
agreement with Beijing High &AMP; New Technology Development Zone
Management Committee for investments in smaller high-tech
projects, high-tech research and development.
</P>
<P>
The company also signed a memorandum of understanding with
Peking University in developing bio-technology research and
manufacturing facilities in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
As the sole overseas listing conglomerate of the Beijing
municipal government, Beijing Enterprises Holdings reported total
revenue and attributable operating profit of 3,371 million HK
dollars (432 million U.S. dollars) and 426 million HK dollars (55
million U.S. dollars) respectively for 1997.  
</P>
