outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party were killed in clashes with
security forces in southeastern Turkey, said an official statement.
</P>
<P>
The statement issued by the office of the Emergency Regional
Rule on Wednesday said 42 PKK militants were killed after the
rebels killed 14 village guards in the areas of Toreli, Anakoy and
Abali of Gevas town of Van province linking Iran.
