<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed mixed Wednesday as profit-taking
subsided but trading remained thin with local institutional
support on selective counters.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index shed 0.82
of a point to 384.22, the all-share Emas Index added 0.06 of a
point to 101.86, the Industrial Index was 13.26 points higher at
778.05 and the Second Board Index gained 0.83 of a point to 97.85.
</P>
<P>
Gainers beat losers 353 to 191 while 155 counters were
unchanged and 217 untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover fell to 94.659 million shares worth 138.063
million ringgit (36.332 million U.S. dollars) from 198.442 million
shares worth 262.454 million ringgit (69.066 million U.S. dollars)
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Main Board turnover shrank to 86.548 million shares worth
127.005 million ringgit (33.422 million U.S. dollars) from
Tuesday's 179.849 million shares valued at 234.830 million ringgit
(61.797 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Second Board turnover fell to 8.111 million shares worth
11.057 million ringgit (2.909 million U.S. dollars) against 18.593
million shares valued at 27.624 million ringgit (7.269 million
U.S. dollars) Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Off-market deals contracted to 3.031 million shares worth
11.859 million ringgit (3.12 million U.S. dollars) compared with
Tuesday's 7.503 million shares valued at 14.502 million ringgit
(3.816 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
On a sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 4.390
million shares traded, industrial products 5.828 million shares,
construction 13.684 million shares, trading/services 27.511
million shares, infrastructure 744,000 shares, finance 7.830
million shares, hotels 54,000 shares, properties 10.686 million
shares, plantation 2.970 million shares, mining 303,800 shares,
trusts 27,000 shares, closed/fund 17,000 shares and loans 12.501
million shares. 
</P>
