<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Some Enterprises Confess Foreign Exchange Fraud </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 14 (Xinhua) -- The State Administration of
Foreign Exchange (SAFE) said today that 344 enterprises have
voluntarily confessed to fraudulent practices in buying foreign
exchange after a decision by SAFE on October 7 urging them to do
so.
</P>
<P>
On October 7, SAFE announced that enterprises that were guilty
of fraudulent transactions that involved less than 5 million
U.S. dollars worth, would be treated leniently if they confessed
their offence voluntarily within 48 hours.
</P>
<P>
A SAFE spokesman said that the 344 enterprises confessed to
fraudulent actions worth 773 million U.S. dollars and 46.57
million HK dollars. Some were involved in fraud that was worth
more than 5 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
According to the spokesman, these enterprises have all said
that they will try to recover the money, which has been remitted
overseas, to reduce state losses.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that SAFE is still investigating some
foreign exchange fraud cases. 
</P>
</TEXT>
