<HEADLINE> Communist Party Central Committee Plenary Session Concluded </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 14 (Xinhua) -- The Third Plenary Session of
the 15th Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC)
was held in Beijing from October 12 to 14 to reach a central
committee decision on certain major issues concerning agriculture
and rural work.
</P>
<P>
General Secretary of the CPC Jiang Zemin spoke at the session
on agricultural development and rural issues.
</P>
<P>
The 185 members and 148 alternate members of the CPC Central
Committee reached a consensus on the importance of agriculture,
rural work, and farmers in China's reforms, opening up, and
modernization.
</P>
<P>
They said that the agricultural base and development and rural
economy needs to be strengthened to increase farmers' incomes.
</P>
<P>
They praised the achievements of the past 20 years and set a
goal for 2010 for economic, political, and cultural development in
rural society and stressed the importance of sticking to existing
economic and distribution practices. They emphasized the
importance of solving key water conservation and environmental
issues and advancing technology.
</P>
<P>
They also reviewed the international and domestic situation and
the work of the Central Committee in the past year and called for
further reforms. 
</P>
