<HEADLINE> Bank Issues Financial Bonds Through Public Bidding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 14 (Xinhua) -- The China State Development
Bank (SDB) today issued 10 billion yuan in financial bonds through
public bidding.
</P>
<P>
The three-year bonds have an annual interest rate of 5.94
percent, which will be paid annually.
</P>
<P>
This was the third time the SDB has issued financial bonds
through public bidding since September 2. The bonds issued include
five billion yuan in one-year bonds and 20 billion yuan in
three-year bonds. Revenue from the bonds will be used for key
state construction projects.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the SDB said these bonds are designed for
commercial banks, city cooperative banks, rural credit
cooperatives and insurance companies.
</P>
<P>
The bonds can be traded through inter-bank facilities with
approval from the People's Bank of China, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that issuing bonds through public bidding is the
first step in the reform of China's policy-oriented banks'
fund-raising mechanism, and that it is significant for reforming
China's investment and fund-raising systems and improving
policy-oriented banks' management mechanism.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that since the SDB was founded in 1994 it
has repaid all principal and interest on mature financial
bonds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
