<HEADLINE> African States Postpone "Blue Crane" Military </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Southern Africa
Development Community (SADC) countries have postponed a joint
military exercise due to the war in the Democratic Republic of
Congo (DRC), media reports said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"Due to the recent events in the sub-region, it has become
necessary to review the feasibility of conducting the Blue Crane
exercise next November as scheduled previously," Tanzanian
newspaper The Guardian Wednesday quoted a defense ministry
