Defense and National Service Tuesday, said a new date for the
military games, scheduled to take place in mid-November in South
Africa, will be announced later after the regional situation is
reviewed.
</P>
<P>
Countries which plan to participate in the "Blue Crane"
exercise include Tanzania, Angola, Botswana, the DRC, Lesotho,
Malawi, Mauritius, Mozambique, Namibia and Seychelles, South
Africa, Swaziland and Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
The operation is to improve the capacity of the SADC military
forces for peace initiatives. Decision to launch the operation
was reached earlier at a meeting of the SADC Inter-State Defense
and Security Committee (ISDSC).
</P>
<P>
At present, four ISDSC members are involved in the war in DRC.
They are the DRC itself, Angola, Namibia and Zimbabwe, which are
jointly fighting against rebels who attempt to topple the
government of President Laurent Kabila. 
