<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> End Of Era in Rural China as Oxen Are Retired (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Ploughing and planting
with the use of oxen is slowly being replaced by farm machines in
the rural parts of China.
</P>
<P>
Dang Erhei, a sixty-year-old farmer in Zhaoxian County in Hebei
Province, is faster than other farmers with his ploughing and
planting, even with his oxen, and has a technique that saves seeds.
</P>
<P>
But, he's not as good as he was in the past, especially this
autumn because his son Dang Suxiao has a machine that ploughs,
plants wheat and harvests corn.
</P>
<P>
Cattle, iron ploughs and drills were the major farm implements
in rural China in the past, but, since the reforms and opening up,
the government has increased the development of farm machinery. It
has also supported farmers in buying farm machines.
</P>
<P>
Dang Suxiao spent 60,000 yuan on his harvester, which brings
about 10,000 yuan in profits annually. Dang gets a bonus and
subsidy from the local government for the purchase. In his
hometown, 82 percent of the 80,000 rural households have tractors
and other implements.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981014.0133 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> End of Era in Rural China as Oxen Are Retired (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dang said that nearly 1,000 rural households have harvesters
and not only help harvest corn at home, but also help harvest
wheat in neighboring Henan Province and the Inner Mongolia
Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
In the country, ploughing, irrigation, plant protection,
threshing, processing and transportation are now basically done by
machines.
</P>
<P>
China has plans to increase agricultural mechanization in
backward areas in the 1996-2000 period, and Dang said that the
days of people like his father have passed.
</P>
<P>
Agricultural mechanization has freed more rural people from
farming and pushed them into the service sector.
</P>
<P>
There are 36.8 million farmers using agricultural machinery in
rural China who have become an important force for agricultural
modernization and industrialization.
</P>
<P>
A study by the State Council's development and research center
reveals that mechanization has also helped develop the breeding
industry and increase farm output.
</P>
<P>
Xu Fengxian, a researcher of the Chinese Academy of Social
Sciences, says that the rapid agricultural mechanization has been
important in agricultural modernization and in developing China's
industrial and service sectors.  
</P>
