<HEADLINE> Four-fifths of African Food Produced by Women: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, October 14 (Xinhua) -- A country representative of
Food and Agriculture Organization (FAO) has disclosed that over
80 percent of the food in Africa is produced by women.
</P>
<P>
While officiating Tuesday at World Food Open Day celebrations
under the theme "Women Feed the World", George Mburathi told the
villagers near Kabwe, 150 kilometers north of Lusaka, that women
play a critical role in food security in Africa, The Post
reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"Over 50 percent of the food produced in the world is by women
and 80 percent in Africa is produced by women," Mburathi said. "
Despite all these efforts they are not recognized because their
production levels are not even reflected in some statistics made
so far."
</P>
<P>
He pointed out if the women can be supported in attaining
their expectations, the hunger situation in Zambia and Africa in
general could be reduced.
</P>
<P>
Mburathi said there is a lot of potential in Zambia that the
women can utilize. He called on the Zambian women to produce more
food and try to feed the whole nation.
</P>
<P>
Zambia, which has a population of 9.6 million and a vast
cultivatable land, imports a large amount of maize each year with
its limited foreign reserves. 
</P>
