<DOCNO> XIE19981014.0151 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shipbuilding Industry Develops Rapidly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 14 (Xinhua) -- China's shipbuilding output
increased to 3.85 million tons in 1997, ranking third in the world
and up from 860,000 tons in 1978 when the reform and opening
policy was initiated.
</P>
<P>
The country's 740 shipbuilding enterprises achieved a combined
industrial value of 26.26 billion yuan last year, according to the
State Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
China is now able to produce the vast majority of ships needed
for overseas and domestic customers, including high-speed vessels and
large container vessels, said an official from the China State
Shipbuilding Corporation (CSSC).
</P>
<P>
The country had a very weak ocean-shipping fleet before 1970,
with 70 percent of its foreign-trade transport volume accomplished
by renting foreign vessels.
</P>
<P>
In 1970s, China built 86 vessels above the 10,000-tonnage
level, with an annual shipbuilding output of 150,000 tons on
average. From 1979 to 1988, the country produced nearly 1.4
million tons of vessels annually on average, and its ship exports
climbed. During the 1990s China's shipbuilding industry has grown
rapidly under sound international market conditions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981014.0152 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Anwar Freed From ISA Detention, but Remanded in Prison </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Former Malaysian deputy
prime minister Anwar Ibrahim was freed Wednesday from detention
under the Internal Security Act (ISA), but taken to the Sungai
Buloh Prison for remand, police said.
</P>
<P>
Confirming this, police officer Yaacob Mohamed Amin of the
police headquarters here said police obtained the order for
Anwar's remand Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Anwar, who was charged with five counts of corrupt practice and
five counts of unnatural sex acts, is being remanded because his
application for bail on four charges of corrupt practice has been
rejected by the High Court. Anwar filed an appeal against the High
Court decision Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Anwar, who pleaded not guilty to all the charges, goes on trial
on four charges of corrupt practice on November 2. Trial dates for
another count of corrupt practice and five charges of sodomy have
yet to be fixed.
</P>
<P>
Anwar was sacked as deputy prime minister and finance minister
on September 2 and was arrested here by police under ISA on
September 20 after he addressed an alleged illegal assembly of his
supporters which resulted in riots in the capital city. 
</P>
