<HEADLINE> Northeastern Chinese Province Expects Record Grain Output </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Grain output in Jilin
Province, a major grain producer in China, is expected to hit an
all-time high this year, according to official estimates.
</P>
<P>
The province is expected to harvest 23.5 billion kg of grain
this year, about 232 million kg more than the previous record in
1996 and more than 5 billion kg more than last year, provincial
authorities say.
</P>
<P>
The is significant because of the many parts of China that
suffered the the worst flooding in several decades this summer. It
will add to Jilin's economic growth by about 3 percentage points,
greatly increasing the chances of meeting the provincial economic
target of 8 to 9 percent this year, analysts say. 
</P>
</TEXT>
