<HEADLINE> Central Chinese Province Increasing Foreign Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Henan Province recently
released a list of 14 preferential policies encouraging local
enterprises to increase exports and economic and technological
cooperation with overseas partners to counter the impact of the
Asian financial crisis and help the province reach its trade goal
this year.
</P>
<P>
All companies in foreign trade and economic cooperation will be
entitled to income tax rebates for three years, and foreign trade
and economic cooperation departments are expected to handle rebate
claims within three working days.
</P>
<P>
Companies are expected to use every possible chance to explore
the market and will attend the Guangzhou Autumn Commodities Fair
which will be open on October 15 and prepare for a provincial
economic and trade fair scheduled for the United States in
November.
</P>
<P>
By late August, Henan had exported 781 million U.S. dollars
worth of commodities, a fall of 5.8 percent from last year,
accounting for 55.7 percent of the province's goal of 1.4 billion
U.S. dollars for this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
