<HEADLINE> World Food Program Aid for Central China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, October 14 ( Xinhua) -- The World Food Program today
provided 28 million U.S. dollars worth of emergency food aid for
Hunan province, one of the most severely hit regions in China
during this summer's flooding.
</P>
<P>
This summer, WFP officials visited flood-damaged parts of Hunan
several times and decided to provide 110,000 tons of wheat for
them.
</P>
<P>
The aid will start being sent to Hunan early this month, mainly
to 7 of the most severely damaged cities and counties.
</P>
<P>
Local sources say that the provincial government will also
provide 33,000 tons of rice and 155 million yuan (18.6 million
U.S. dollars) for sheltering flood victims, repairing farms and
irrigation ditches, and building village roads.  
