<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Hospital Helps Comatose Patients Recover </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, October 142 (Xinhua) -- Doctors at the Heilongjiang
Provincial Rehabilitation Hospital in northeast China's
Heilongjiang have helped 142 comatose patients take a turn for the
better.
</P>
<P>
Thirty of them have completely recovered and 4 others are now
living a normal life and have returned to their work.
</P>
<P>
The hospital often helps patients recover consciousness
in about 40 days, and has a record of 7 days.
</P>
<P>
The patients in a comatose state have suffered head
injuries. The hospital started doing research on treatment and
rehabilitation for comatose patients in 1991 and has developed
methods of treating the comatose patients with hyperbaric
oxygenation, traditional Chinese medicine, nutrition, acupuncture,
massage, and electro-therapy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
