<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Direct Foreign Investment Up in Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Direct foreign investment in
Thailand in terms of U.S. dollars rose to 3.3 billion dollars in
the first seven months of this year.
</P>
<P>
The amount almost doubled the 1.8 billion dollars in the same
period of last year, the government said in a press release
received Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The current account has improved during the first seven months
of this year, with a surplus of 8.2 billion dollars. The capital
movement shows a deficit of 7.7 billion dollars, compared with the
4.3 billion dollars in the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, internal economic stability shows some positive
indicators as inflation rate during the first nine months of this
year was at 9.2 percent and it decreased drastically in the third
quarter of 1998 thanks to the stability of currency exchange.
</P>
<P>
But the industrial productivity during the first seven months
of this year declined by 15.9 percent from the same period last
year in almost every sector except textiles.
</P>
<P>
The value of exports in baht currency rose by 56.6 percent in
the first seven months of this year, compared with the same period
of last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
