<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zhejiang's Consumer Market Active </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, October 14 (Xinhua) -- The consumer goods market in
east China's Zhejiang Province continued active last
month, official figures indicate.
</P>
<P>
The province's retail sales volume for consumer goods totaled
15.48 billion yuan in September, up 10 percent over the same
month last year, according to the latest figures provided by
the provincial statistics bureau.
</P>
<P>
Retail sales of consumer goods hit 136.62 billion yuan for the
first nine months, an increase of 9 percent on a yearly basis.
</P>
<P>
The most active items include household electrical appliances,
jewels and foodstuffs.
</P>
<P>
Prices for such goods as building materials, meat and egg have
rebounded as market activity increased.  
</P>
