<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tibetan Mountaineering Team Conquers Mt. Lhotse </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, October 13 (Xinhua) -- The Tibetan mountaineering team
on Tuesday successfully scaled 8,516-meter Mt. Lhotse, the fourth
highest peak in the world.
</P>
<P>
The five-man expedition started off from a 7,900-meter high
camp at 6:15 am and spent little more than four hours reaching
the zenith.
</P>
<P>
The famous climbing team, in their latest bid to conquer all
the 14 mountains higher than 8,000 meters above sea level in the
world, began their adventure more than one month ago on September
8.
</P>
<P>
By May, they had successfully scaled eight out of the 14
mountains.
</P>
<P>
Mt. Lhotse, located along the border between China and Nepal,
is still to be conquered for the first time from the Chinese side
for the treacherous conditions there. 
</P>
</TEXT>
