<HEADLINE> Myanmar Is Trying to Develop Information Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar is trying to formulate a
master plan for the development of the country's information
technology, Lieutenant-General Khin Nyunt was quoted as saying by
Wednesday's official newspaper The New Light of Myanmar.
</P>
<P>
He urged local technicians to work closely with those of fellow
members of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) like
Singapore and Malaysia in preparing to carry out the related
projects,
</P>
<P>
At an information technology forum here Tuesday, sponsored by
the XYBASE Technologies of Malaysia and the Mastech Co Ltd of
Myanmar, First Secretary of the Myanmar State Peace and
Development Council Khin Nyunt disclosed that the government has
been importing annually tens of thousands of computers with very
little tariff, classifying them as education aids and priority
items.
</P>
<P>
Khin Nyunt, who is also the chairman of the Myanmar Computer
Science Development Committee, stressed the importance of the
communication sector, one of the major fields of the information
technology, with the installation of X-25 Packet Switching System
and the provision of E-mail and data communication services to
customers by the Myanmar Post and Telecommunication Authorities
as well as the access of internet to the private sector within a
short time.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar promulgated its Computer Technology Development Law on
September 30, 1996, and later founded the Computer Technology
Development Council. 
