<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Hold Investment Seminars in China, Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh will hold two
international investment seminars in China and Japan separately
this month as part of its campaign for attracting foreign
investment, the Board of Investment (BOI) told Xinhua Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A two-day seminar on "Sino-Bangladesh Trade and Investment"
will begin in China's capital of Beijing on October 16, and a
10-member Bangladeshi team will attend the seminar, jointly
organized by the BOI and China Business monthly, a BOI official
said.
</P>
<P>
This is for the first time Bangladesh is holding such seminar
in China, he noted, adding that representatives of about 100
Chinese corporations are expected to attend the seminar.
</P>
<P>
The BOI will hold another seminar in Tokyo, Japan, on October
23-24 and a 19-member Bangladeshi team will join the seminar and
present papers elaborating the government policies, specially
taken for the foreign investors, he added.
</P>
<P>
The members of the team will also participate in the Global
Business Opportunities Convention-1998 to be held in Osaka, Japan,
on October 19-21, he added.
</P>
<P>
As part of its continuous efforts to attract the foreign
investment, the BOI has held several seminars in Singapore, the
United States and Britain.
</P>
<P>
The Bangladeshi government is strongly committed to attracting
direct foreign investment in different sectors such as
infrastructure development, power and gas, telecommunications,
transport, housing, textiles, cement and steel plants, agro-based
industries, as well as sea and air ports building, according to
the BOI.
</P>
<P>
From July 1,1996, to December 31,1997, a total of 2,137
projects were registered with the BOI worth an estimated 3.4
billion U.S. dollars, the latest figures of the BOI show. 
</P>
</TEXT>
