<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese More Aware of Illness Caused by Air Conditioners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 14 (Xinhua) -- A recent survey reveals that
urban residents in China have become more aware of illness caused
by air conditioners as they enjoy the cool created by the
appliances in summer.
</P>
<P>
The survey, carried out among 1,043 air-conditioner users in
five major cities including Beijing, Shanghai and Guangzhou,
reveals that 88.4 percent of the respondents have heard of
"air-conditioning sickness."
</P>
<P>
Some 473 people, or 45.3 percent of the respondents, believe
"air-conditioning sickness" is really a disease, while 35.9
percent thought otherwise. The remaining 18.8 percent were unsure.
</P>
<P>
Medical specialists at home and abroad have acknowledged the
existence of "air-conditioning sickness," and some experts have
said that closed rooms stop the circulation of fresh air and
easily become a breeding ground for germs.
</P>
<P>
And people can easily catch cold when they suddenly step out
of a cool room into the scorching heat, they add.
</P>
<P>
About 50 percent of those surveyed said the cool produced by
air conditioners usually cause a cold, stuffy nose or dizziness,
reactions similar to those found in medical studies.
</P>
<P>
Experts advise that those using air conditioners not keep it on
around the clock, and not keep the indoor temperature more than
seven degrees lower than outside.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981014.0196 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Bosnian-Herzegovina Presidency Sworn in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, October 13 (Xinhua) -- The three newly elected members
of the Presidency of Bosnian and Herzegovina were inaugurated
Tuesday in Sarajevo.
</P>
<P>
Zivko Radisic, Ante Jelavic and Alija Izetbegovic, representing
the Serb, Croat and Muslim communities respectively, were elected
in the mid-September elections conducted in accordance with the
Dayton peace agreements.
</P>
<P>
Radisic will serve as new chairman of the presidency for the
first eight months of the four year mandate.
</P>
<P>
After being sworn in, he said the new presidency had started to
exercise power to bring Bosnia-Herzegovina into a new stage marked
by the implementation of the Dayton accord and the strengthening
of peace and development.
</P>
<P>
He noted that their task was to prove that they were willing
to work, and capable of working for the people, peace and progress.
</P>
<P>
Jelavic hoped that the new presidency would demonstrate
reconciliation and endurance, and thoroughly implement the Dayton
peace accord together with the international community.
</P>
<P>
He suggested there be immediate efforts to work on plans for
refugee returns and reduce military forces so that more money
would be spared for home rebuilding.
</P>
<P>
Izetbegovic, former chairman of the presidency, said he hoped
the new leading group would implement the Dayton peace agreements
and safeguard the rights and interests of the voters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
