<HEADLINE> Myanmar Leader Praises Enhanced Relation with Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar leader
Lieutenant-General Khin Nyunt has praised the enhanced relation
and cooperation between his country and Malaysia brought about
through assistance and encouragement of both governments.
</P>
<P>
Khin Nyunt, first secretary of the Myanmar State Peace and
Development Council, made the appraisal here Tuesday at an
information technology forum, jointly sponsored by the XYBASE
Technologies of Malaysia and the Mastech Co Ltd of Myanmar.
</P>
<P>
He said "Myanmar and Malaysia, as brother members of ASEAN
(Association of Southeast Asian Nations), share many similar
characteristics and these similarities facilitate the
collaboration with each other."
</P>
<P>
"The leaders of the two countries have exchanged visits and
held high level talks with mutually beneficial results," he added.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that "at a time when countries of Asia are
trying to defend against the interference of some big powers in
the political and the economic areas through unity and solidarity,
the growing cooperation between Myanmar and Malaysia will benefit
not just our two countries but also the entire region as well."
</P>
<P>
He urged ASEAN and Asian brothers to collectively defend
against the negative Western concepts, outlooks and culture which
are incompatible with the cultural and traditional values of ASEAN
and Asian nations.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar and Malaysia established diplomatic relation in early
1958. The exchange of visits between their leaders in the recent
two years has significantly contributed to the further development
of their ties and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia has brought in Myanmar a capital of 587.17 million
U.S. dollars in 25 projects by the end of March this year,
standing as the fourth largest investor in the country after
Singapore, Britain and Thailand. 
</P>
</TEXT>
