<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka's Per Capita Income Projected to Go Up to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan Industrial
Development Ministry has projected that the country's per capita
income will go up to 860 U.S. dollars at the end of this year, the
ministry sources said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The projection is based on the steady increase in export
earnings leading to a marked growth rate in the economy, the
sources pointed out.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry expects a significant increase in Gross Domestic
Product (GDP) this year as a result of the increase in export
earnings.
</P>
<P>
The per capita income increased to 814 U.S. dollars in 1997
from 760 U.S. dollars in 1996.
</P>
<P>
From January to July 1998 export earnings recorded a
significant growth rate of 8.4 percent and if this trend continues
during the rest of the year, the projected per capita income would
be a reality, the sources added. 
