<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka To Set Up Rubber Small Holdings Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka will set up the
Rubber Small Holdings Authority before the end of this year to
improve the lot of rubber small holders who are facing hardships
due to depressed prices, according to the Rubber Development
Department here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Legislation for this purpose has been prepared by the
Plantations Ministry and will be presented to the Cabinet soon for
approval, the department sources said.
</P>
<P>
Under the proposed authority, rubber small holders development
societies will be set up islandwide for the benefit of those who
own rubber lands below 10 acres in extent.
</P>
<P>
These societies will take measures to uplift the living
conditions and provide solutions for the depressed markets now
encountered by the small holders.
</P>
<P>
The authority will also start a special pension scheme for
small holders through these societies. The latex produced by small
holders will also be purchased by the societies at a fair price,
the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The ongoing price crisis faced by the small-scale rubber
producers compelled the ministry to set up this new authority,
said the sources, adding that the authority is expected to
function as the leading institute for the development of the
rubber industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
