<HEADLINE> Argentine Baby Receives Successful Heart Transplant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, October 13 (Xinhua) -- A four-day-old Argentinian
baby has undergone a successful heart transplant in the first
successful operation of its kink in Latin America.
</P>
<P>
The operation at the Children's Hospital of La Plata, Buenos
Aires, lasted 10 hours and was completed at 5:00 a.m. on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Juan Jose Mussi, the health minister of Buenos Aires, said the
baby was recovering in a stable condition.
</P>
<P>
"This is the first surgery of its kind in Latin America due to
the young age of both the donor and recipient," he said.
</P>
<P>
Hospital director Herminia Itarte said that the child was born
with ventricular hypoplasia and atresia, requiring an urgent heart
transplant.
</P>
<P>
The donor organ was taken from a 16-day-old baby who died of a
cerebral malformation. After the child's cause of death was
established the parents agreed to allow the heart to be used in a
transplant.
</P>
<P>
"In spite of the pain the death of a child incurs, they agreed
to donate their baby's heart to save another life," said Itarte.
</P>
</TEXT>
