<HEADLINE> WB-Financed Sewage Treatment Plant to be Built in Dalian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, October 14 (Xinhua) -- A contract to provide technology
and equipment for a sewage treatment plant with World Bank
financing was signed here recently in this port city of northeast
China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
The 100-million-yuan contract was inked between the Dalian
Drainage Works Corporation and the Shenyang Technological Import
and Export Company, the Philipp Muller Company of Germany, and the
Shenyang Environmental Protection Group.
</P>
<P>
It will be an important part of the construction of a sewage
treatment project at Malanhe in Dalian and is scheduled to be put
in to use before the end of next year, said a local official.
</P>
<P>
The Malanhe sewage treatment project will cost 330 million yuan
(about 39.76 million U.S. dollars), of which 10 million
U.S. dollars will be covered by loans provided by the World Bank.
</P>
<P>
The project includes construction of a sewage treatment
facility with a daily capacity of 120,000 tons, installation of
six-km-long pipelines, and construction of two sewage pumping
stations.  
</P>
