<HEADLINE> Northeast China's Shenyang Strives to Become Best Tourist City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Shenyang, a heavy industrial
city in northeast China's Liaoning Province, has been trying hard
to become one of the country's best tourist destinations and turn
tourism into an important source of income.
</P>
<P>
Over the past years, Shenyang, also the provincial capital of
Liaoning, has lavished huge investments in improving urban
infrastructure and environment in response to the call
three years ago from the China National Tourism Administration to
build China's best tourist cities.
</P>
<P>
And now, tourists to Shenyang will find it has become an easier
place to tour with the completion of the second ring road, built
at cost of 1.5 billion yuan, renovation of an urban canal, 21
refurbished cultural squares, and six new shopping streets.
</P>
<P>
The city is also home to 100 important cultural sites and
many places associated with well-known people. It also has plenty
of picturesque natural scenery.
</P>
<P>
Efforts in afforestation have brought Shenyang's forest cover
to 30.67 percent, much higher than the national average. Shenyang
also has been chosen by the United Nations as an experimental
center for sustainable urban development.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the city had 13.46 million tourist arrivals,
including 152,000 from overseas, and earnings generated by tourism
contributed 6.9 percent of the city's gross domestic product (GDP)
in 1997.  
</P>
</TEXT>
