<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> High Jumper Aims at Higher Goals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Zhang Xiaoxiang began high
jumping for the first time at nine to improve his health, but
then he found he can neven leave it.
</P>
<P>
Zhang is a member of the Chinese delegation for the '98
International Schoolsports Federation (ISF) World Gymnasiade,
which opened on Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
A 17-year-old at the city's Datong Senior High School, Zhang
Began his high jump training when he was still a primary school
student.
</P>
<P>
Now 1.88 meters tall, Zhang has become a strong boy sportsman
and has a personal best of 2.1 meters.
</P>
<P>
This achievement comes from years of hard training. Everyday
after school, Zhang attends regualr training which lasts one to
two hours.
</P>
<P>
"I usually get home at six in the afternoon. After the
training, I felt to tired to study, so I try to make full use of
the noon rest time to finish my homework," Zhang said.
</P>
<P>
"I'm only 17 years old and still far from the peak of my
career," he said. "My trainer said I can clear 2.2 meters. I will
work harder for that." 
</P>
</TEXT>
