<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreign Investment in Vietnam Declines Over 9 Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam licensed an additional
178 foreign-invested projects with a combined capital of nearly
1.7 billion U.S. dollars over the past nine months, accounting for
48 percent and 42 percent of the number of projects and
investment capital, respectively, for the same period last year,
according to an official report.
</P>
<P>
Of the new projects, 62 projects worth 33 million U.S. dollars
are involved in industrial production, 47 projects valued at 42
million U.S. dollars are in the agro-forestry-fisheries and
aquatic produce processing sectors, and 18 other projects worth
86.6 million U.S. dollars are in the construction sector.
</P>
<P>
Singapore has been the leading foreign capital investor in
Vietnam this year with 22 projects worth nearly 792 million U.S.
dollars, followed by Britain with three projects worth 210 million
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam has 2,048 effective foreign-invested projects to date
with a combined investment capital of over 33.9 billion U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
These projects created regular jobs for 270,000 workers, and
indirectly created jobs for 150,000 others. 
</P>
</TEXT>
