<HEADLINE> TV Documentary Will Show Tibet's Today, Yesterday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, October 14 (Xinhua) -- People at home and abroad will be
able to learn about the yesterday and today of Tibet by watching a
15-part TV documentary.
</P>
<P>
The documentary will introduce the folk customs, tourism, and
social and economic growth of Tibet in its nearly three-hour-long
presentation, production of which is expected to be completed
before July 1999.
</P>
<P>
The Tibet Regional Tourism Administration and E'mei Film Studio
of Sichuan Province have co-invested one million yuan (about
120,000 U.S. dollars) in the documentary.
</P>
<P>
The documentary aims to inform the world about the true Tibet
and bring Tibet closer to the rest of the world, an official from
the Tourism Administration said. Next year marks the 50th
anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China and
the 40th anniversary of the democratic reform in Tibet.
</P>
<P>
The documentary will be released worldwide in both Chinese and
English.  
</P>
