<HEADLINE> East China City Seeking Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Taizhou, a coastal city in east
China's Zhejiang Province, announced 500 projects here Tuesday
opened to overseas investment and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The projects, which will involve a total investment of 12.5
billion U.S. dollars, include infrastructure, exploitation of
natural resources and transformation of traditional industries
such as electro-machinery, pharmaceuticals, tourism and chemicals.
</P>
<P>
Among the major projects are a thermo power plant, the
Maotoushan Nuclear Power Plant and the port of Taizhou.
</P>
<P>
The offer, announced at the Taizhou Investment Talks held here
Tuesday, has attracted more than 100 overseas investors.
</P>
<P>
Taizhou, with rich energy resources and a long coastline, aims
to become the largest power base and a major port in east China.
</P>
<P>
The city now has over 600 foreign-funded enterprises with a
total investment of 760 million U.S. dollars.  
</P>
