<HEADLINE> Seven Arrested in 400 kg Heroin Haul in Australia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Seven people were arrested and
a ship was under police escort early Wednesday morning after what
Australian police calls the largest ever heroin seizure in the
country.
</P>
<P>
Up to 400 kilograms of heroin worth up to 240 million U.S.
dollars was seized after the drug was transferred from a ship to a
smaller vessel on the New South Wales state's mid-north coast,
southeast Australia, the Australian Federal Police (AFP) said.
</P>
<P>
An AFP spokeswoman said the heroin seizure was believed to be
the largest ever in Australia.
</P>
<P>
She said there was no information about the nationalities of
the seven people arrested.
</P>
<P>
Australian Federal Customs Minister Warren Truss told reporters
the seizure was the biggest in Australian history.
</P>
<P>
"We have seizures almost every second day but a major seizure
of this order, the biggest in our history, is a demonstration that
our techniques are working effectively."
</P>
<P>
"Taking this amount of heroin out of the Australian market will
obviously have a significant impact. It is several hundred million
dollars worth of heroin so that obviously make a significant dent
in the trade," said the minister. 
</P>
