<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Finalizes Over 200 Smuggling Cases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Beijing Customs authorities
finalized 211 smuggling cases during the first eight months of this
year, with the value of confiscated goods approaching 520 million
yuan (65 million US dollars), a dramatic 170 percent rise on the
previous year's figure.
</P>
<P>
Customs sources point to a considerable rise in the volume of
counterfeit documents used to evade payment of tariffs.
</P>
<P>
Major smuggled items include telecommunications equipment,
chemical fibers and automobiles. State-owned and
collective enterprises have been heavily implicated in smuggling
cases. 
</P>
</TEXT>
