<HEADLINE> England Soccer Fans Ordered Home </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Twentyfive England soccer fans,
who are on their way to Luxembourg for an European soccer
Championship qualifying match, were arrested in Belgium and would
be sent home before the game starts, a Foreign Office spokeswoman
said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"Belgian police have arrested 25 England fans. They have been
detained pending deportation, which we understand will take place
tomorrow (Wednesday)," she said.
</P>
<P>
She added that the 25 fans were being held in a transit area
at Brussels airport.
</P>
<P>
Belgian police accused the fans of being drunk and a menace to
public order as they travelled through Belgium to Luxembourg.
</P>
