<HEADLINE> Makinen Extends Lead Despite Spin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, October 13 (Xinhua) -- World champion Tommi Makinen of
Finland stayed on course for his first San Remo Rally victory on
Tuesday despite a spin on stage 15.
</P>
<P>
The Mitsubishi driver wasted 12 seconds from a spin on the
day's seventh stage, but he set the fastest times on the final
three stages to establish a hefty 28.5 seconds lead over Italian
Liatti in a Subaru.
</P>
<P>
Liatti's Subaru teammate Colin McRae of Britain finished the
leg 54.2 seconds further behind.
</P>
<P>
McRae and Makinen trail the fourth-placed world championship
leader Carlos Sainz of Spain by nine points in the title race
with only the British RAC Rally ahead after San Remo. 
</P>
