<HEADLINE> Paper Food Container Plant Starts Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, October 14 (Xinhua) -- China's largest paper food
container producer commenced operation on October 5 and plans to
join the national effort to eliminate the "white pollution".
</P>
<P>
The plant, completed at a cost of 88 million yuan, has an
annual production capacity of 500 million paper food
containers.
</P>
<P>
The plant, located in central China's Henan Province, is
expected to greatly reduce the massive demand for styrofoam
containers.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that China's mushrooming fast-food sector uses
over 10 billion styrofoam containers a year. Nearly half of them
are discarded along China's railways, causing white pollution.
</P>
<P>
The low cost paper boxes will be recyclable. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981014.0269 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NBA Cancels First Two Weeks of Season as Labor Talks Stall </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 13 (Xinhua) -- The NBA canceled games for
the first time in its 52-year history today, wiping out the
season's first two weeks after collective bargaining with the
Players Association again bogged down.
</P>
<P>
"This is not a very pleasant announcement," NBA commissioner
David Stern said from a Manhattan hotel. "The realities are I
think the owners had no choice."
</P>
<P>
"Lousy, disappointed. My job is to put on games for the fans,
not to cancel them. It's terribly disappointing," Stern added.
</P>
<P>
However, both sides expressed optimism about a luxury tax
proposed by the union that Stern said the owners would respond to
by Friday.
</P>
<P>
Players Association executive director Billy Hunter said the
proposal also included the reinstitution of restricted free
agency and a policy on marijuana but would retain the Larry Bird
Exception, which all teams to exceed the salary cap to sign their
own free agents.
</P>
<P>
"Obviously we're concerned the league has elected to cancel
games, but we're buoyed by their agreeability," Hunter said.
"There has been some progress."
</P>
<P>
A total of 99 games were scheduled over the first 14 days of
the season, which was to begin November 3. The entire preseason
schedule was canceled last week, when the union and league met
for the first time in two months.
</P>
<P>
"It's evident we're not going to reach an agreement any time
soon, so we are reluctantly canceling the first two weeks, "
deputy commissioner Russ Granik said.
</P>
<P>
The NBA had been the only major American professional sport
that had never lost a game due to a labor dispute. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
