<DOCNO> XIE19981014.0274 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lewis-Holyfield Fight set for Early </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Evander Holyfield and Lennox
Lewis may have a chance to fight for a world title early next
year.
</P>
<P>
Promoters Don King and Panos Eliades said on Tuesday that they
had agreed a deal to go ahead with a fight in February or March.
The fight is set to provide the first undisputed world champion
since Mike Tyson unified the titles in 1987.
</P>
<P>
World Boxing Association (WBA) and International Boxing
Federation (IBF) champion Holyfield and World Boxing Council(WBC)
title-holder Lewis have yet to sign contracts, even though the
boxer's financial demands appear to have been met.
</P>
<P>
The promoters hope agreement can be reached in principle by
Friday. "The fight is on. I have already talked to Evander and
the fight is on," Holyfield promoter King said. "We do not want
no outs.
</P>
<P>
"It is very important that this fight takes place. The
credibility of boxing is in the doldrums...It's reality. It's no
longer a dream."
</P>
<P>
"We have done the deal and agreed terms, " Eliades added.
</P>
<P>
"Don's job is to get Evander to sign the contract and I have
to get Lennox to sign the contract...There is no fight until both
contracts have been signed by both, however."
</P>
<P>
The promoters have set two possible dates for the fight --
February 27 or March 6. King said no venue had yet been set but
he said South Africa had shown a great deal of interest in
staging the event.
</P>
<P>
"I'll go wherever I can get the money," King said. "South
Africa are interested...Now there is no site but we will find
one."
</P>
<P>
If South Africa does not come off, it is more than likely that
the casino tables of Las Vegas will provide the backdrop.
</P>
<P>
A re-match has also been written into the deal, hammered out
by King and Eliades in nearly seven hours of talks in London on
Monday, should Briton Lewis win the fight.
</P>
<P>
American Holyfield, now 36, has indicated he would like to
unify the three main titles before retiring in 2000. Lewis,
33,has been chasing the unified world title since winning the
Seoul Olympic gold medal for Canada a decade ago.
</P>
<P>
King, never prone to understatement, has called Lewis "the
most wanted man on planet earth".
</P>
<P>
"Evander is hungry for it, we are after him," he said. "We are
here to talk about Lewis -- the unknown champion that is going to
become visible.
</P>
<P>
"He has been playing the invisible man but we are going to
bring him into full visibility, " he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
