<HEADLINE> Shanghai Anticipates Record Autumn Grain Harvest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 14 (Xinhua) -- This year's per unit autumn
grain yield in Shanghai, China's leading commercial and financial
center, is expected to set a new record.
</P>
<P>
The per hectare autumn grain yield is expected to hit 8,250 kg,
according to the Municipal Agriculture and Forestry
Bureau. Shanghai has planted autumn grain crops on 233,000 hectares.
</P>
<P>
The per hectare autumn grain output for a suburban experimental
zone is expected to hit 10,455 kg, some 24.8 percent above the
local average, according to the bureau.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai's annual grain output is expected to reach two billion
kilograms. 
</P>
</TEXT>
