<HEADLINE> Tibet Opens Model Agriculture Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Construction of the first modern
agriculture demonstration zone in suburban Doilungdeqen County of
Lhasa, capital of the Tibet Autonomous Region, commenced tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The 933-ha zone, which will be completed at an estimated cost
of 5.58 million yuan (674,000 US dollars), will increase farmland
land coverage in the area which is criss-crossed by sand and
gravel roads lined with trees and canals.
</P>
<P>
Some 167 hectares of irrigated farmland will be added and the
grain output is expected to hit 7,500 kg per hectare. The annual
per capita income of farmers is expected to rise to over 2,000
yuan, up 400 yuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
