<HEADLINE> Zhejiang Preparing for Expressway Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Preparations for construction
of an expressway linking major cities in east China's Zhejiang
Province are progressing smoothly.
</P>
<P>
The planned 175-km Ningbo-Jinhua Expressway, projected to cost
five billion yuan, will run through the cities of Fenghua,
Shengzhou, Dongyang and Yiwu. The mileage of the new expressway is
33 percent less than the combined length of existing highways in
the region, according to official of the Ningbo Transportation
Committee.
</P>
<P>
The major industrial and commercial cities of Ningbo, Shaoxing
and Jinhua are also located along the expressway. Beilun Port in
Ningbo handles more than 10 percent of Zhejiang's annual
import-export volume.
</P>
<P>
The expressway will facilitate commercial exchanges and
cooperation between the aforementioned cities and surrounding
areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
