<HEADLINE> France Completes Nerve Gas Tests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
UNITED NATIONS, October 13 (Xinhua) -- France had completed
its tests of whether warhead fragments found in Iraq contained
traces of the deadly nerve gas sX, but did not announce
the results, a U.N. diplomat said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Richard Butler, Executive Chairman of the United Nations
Special Commission in charge of dismantling Iraq's weapons of
mass destruction, told the Security Council this morning that
the results would be evaluated by experts on October 22 and 23,
Council President Jeremy Greenstock told reporters.
</P>
<P>
According to U.N. sources, attending the meeting on October
22 and 23 will be experts from the American, French and Swiss
laboratories as well as participants from Russia and Britain.
