<HEADLINE> Dow Dips 63 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, October 13 (Xinhua) -- U.S. stocks pulled back on
Tuesday, mostly affected by the report of lower sales in the third
quarter by Eastman Kodak, a blue-chip component.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average closed 63.33 points lower at
7938.14 after recovering from a 116-point loss which put the index
below this year's starting point, 7908.25.
</P>
<P>
The Dow, which had gained almost 550 points from Thursday's
low, suffered an equivalent of nearly 50 point loss from Kodak,
which reported a 72 percent earnings' growth over last year's
third quarter, but it saw a 10 percent drop in sales and foresaw a
not so encouraging fourth-quarter update.
</P>
<P>
Broader market indicators also pulled back, with the
technology-heavy Nasdaq composite index falling 36.64 to 1509.44.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index inched back 2.91 to 994.80. The
New York Stock Exchange composite index was down 0.81 to 492.14
and the American Stock Exchange composite index was down 3.15 to
577.86.
</P>
<P>
Preliminary calculations show that declining issues led
advancers by a 4-3 margin on NYSE whose volume turned up to 725.88
million shares from 688.26 million previously. 
</P>
</TEXT>
